level setting, um, I'm actually literally have it open right now, working on our

00:06:06.440 --> 00:06:11.959
like next fiscal year's, um, targets for the hospital system I worked for.

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.320
Um, so yeah, just really curious to get like your perspective on some of the

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:21.799
non-financial, um, metrics that you guys keep track of and if and how you do.

00:06:22.760 --> 00:06:23.839
Um, set for those.

00:06:24.359 --> 00:06:24.920
Yeah, we do.

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:28.799
We're actually building a platform to do general hierarchical forecasting

00:06:28.799 --> 00:06:30.239
for any metric at Stripe.

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:31.839
And so we've expanded this.

00:06:31.839 --> 00:06:36.119
We do some sales planning right now, which is a little bit financial.

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:41.720
Um, we do it for our active users and we're using, looking at things like, uh,

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:47.399
like uptime as well, like how, how much, um, should we expect, you know, Stripe to

00:06:47.399 --> 00:06:52.720
be live and yeah, so the, we generally find that the approaches, oh, and we also

00:06:52.720 --> 00:06:56.600
do a lot in ops too, so capacity planning for our support volume, support tickets.

00:06:56.600 --> 00:07:00.279
Um, we've found that the methods are pretty similar across, you know, all

00:07:00.279 --> 00:07:05.079
of these types of problems is there's a lot of nuance in terms of, uh, making

00:07:05.079 --> 00:07:08.679
sure that you capture the data correctly and capture, actually solve the business

00:07:08.679 --> 00:07:09.000
problem, right?

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.079
You can't just sort of throw a general forecasting method at something, but,

00:07:12.559 --> 00:07:16.040
um, but we have found in general that the, the hierarchical format works really

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:19.640
well in a business setting and that, you know, you often care about some more

00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:22.399
detailed dimensions and then you also care about adding up to the whole.

00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:25.000
Crystal, I see you asked a question in the chat too.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:25.760
Do you want to jump in?

00:07:31.839 --> 00:07:34.359
And maybe I miss, I can ask that, that one too.

