So we are still early days, but we're pretty enthusiastic.

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:20.160
Um, we've done a lot of NLP work generally on the upside.

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:25.640
So we classify our issues using BERT, which is sort of a previous generation

00:08:25.640 --> 00:08:27.000
natural language processing model.

00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:32.400
Um, and you know, that allows us to know what kind of, uh, questions are

00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:36.000
getting asked and what topics are support issues are about, which we then

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.960
use to direct a lot of internal efforts.

00:08:37.960 --> 00:08:41.799
Like where should we be, you know, making updates or, uh, bug fixes in

00:08:41.799 --> 00:08:43.840
our product based on what the support tickets are about.

